<?xml version='1.0' encoding='UTF-8'?>
<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1917-12-03T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1917-12-03T17:00:00-05:00" n="268" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d268">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 656.119/89a</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                the Minister in the Netherlands</hi> (<persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_GJW1" type="to"><hi rend="italic">Garrett</hi></persName>)</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1917-12-03T17:00:00-05:00">
                                    <hi rend="italic">December 3, 1917, 5 p.m.</hi>
                                </date>
                            </dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>811. After consultation with <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_MVC1">McCormick</persName> it has been decided negotiations of agreement
                            with Holland should be carried on in London. <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_MVC1">McCormick</persName> returning
                            from Paris this week to take up this question with British and French
                            and will try to reach some understanding.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="frus1917Supp02v01#p_LR1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Lansing</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>